        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 9:35PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 935 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles south of Bethune, or 16 miles southeast of Stratton, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Kit
Carson County.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 170 and 181.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
